Validating input by throwing and catching exceptions is bad practice. The general advise is to check and validate all kinds of conditions that you can reasonably expect, and only catch and throw exceptions for the situations that you cannot foresee. When you write a try-catch clause, you are assuming that some error might happen for some reason out of your control but you don&#39;t know why, where or how. throwing exceptions is for errors, not just for normal foreseeable program flow.

